# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Atlas environment — copy to .env.local and fill in for backend work.
# The demo app runs with NONE of these set (data is in-memory).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase (Postgres + RLS + storage) — docs/02-architecture.md §3
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# App runtime connection — Supabase TRANSACTION pooler (port 6543).
# Required so connections return to the pooler after each transaction; the
# postgres-js client sets prepare:false (transaction mode can't reuse prepared
# statements). Session mode (port 5432) pins one connection per client and
# exhausts the pooler's client cap under normal concurrency. (Connect →
# Transaction pooler in the Supabase dashboard.)
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...@...pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres
#
# Migrations-only connection — SESSION pooler / direct (port 5432). DDL runs in
# multi-statement transactions that need a session-pinned connection.
# DIRECT_URL=postgresql://...@...pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
#
# Per-process pool size (default 5). Lower to 1 on serverless (Vercel), where
# every instance opens its own pool against the shared pooler cap.
# DB_POOL_MAX=5

# Public base URL used to build links inside emails (invite/nudge CTAs point at
# ${APP_URL}/auth/confirm and ${APP_URL}/me). Defaults to http://localhost:3000.
# APP_URL=https://atlas.twistag.com

# Local ephemeral Postgres for adversarial RLS tests. Leave unset and
# embedded-postgres boots one automatically; set to reuse a system Postgres.
# DATABASE_URL_TEST=

# Auth: Supabase Auth (native magic links + custom access-token hook), NOT
# Stytch — see docs/adrs/002-supabase-auth-not-stytch.md. No separate auth
# creds: it uses the Supabase keys above. Two dashboard config steps are needed
# for production sign-in email (see Resend below).

# Anthropic (Claude) — services/llm
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Resend (transactional email) — services/email
# Invite + nudge emails go out via Resend directly (React Email templates). With
# no RESEND_API_KEY the send no-ops and logs `[email] skipped…`, so dev runs with
# zero email config.
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# EMAIL_FROM="Atlas <hello@atlas.twistag.com>"
#
# Sign-in magic-link email is sent by Supabase Auth, not this app. To make it
# production-ready, in the Supabase dashboard: (1) set Resend as the custom SMTP
# provider, (2) edit the Magic Link template to include {{ .Token }} (the 6-digit
# code) and bump the OTP/link expiry to 24h.

# Inngest (workers)
# INNGEST_EVENT_KEY=
# INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY=
